{
  "stem": "13079.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And his function in Dachau was to develop a specific for malaria, because quinine was hardly available due to the war that was being carried on in the Pacific.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Shilling's part was using-- in the operation of the camp-- was to use these prisoners as guinea pigs to further his work in experimenting upon developing a specific for malaria.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Shilling was a man of advanced years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Being as old as I am now, he was younger than I am now, but I'm 83.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Shilling at the time he was in camp was in his late 60s or early 70s.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He would take these prisoners and have them exposed to [INAUDIBLE] mosquitoes that had malaria.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he would take a little cage out of wire and strap it on to the five prisoners.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mosquito would feed on the prisoner for a while.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he would develop malaria.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then it was the doctor's job to try to develop something that would cure that malaria.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then during the course of his work, many, many prisoners died, because the path that he chose was to develop a-- a specific, which was mercurial in nature.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as a result of it, many of these prisoners died from kidney diseases that were developed as a result of their absorbing lots of mercurial substances.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And during the examination of Dr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Shilling, it was the only thing that sort of shook me a little bit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because here was a man of stature.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he got on the stand there and started lying about he-- his treatment of the prisoners and that he did not take a prisoner that was emaciated, as a guinea pig, but those who seemed to be physically able to serve as proper subjects.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
